	<div class="course-item-content">

<p>Every lesson includes the following types of exercises:</p>

<p>
<strong>Dialogue.</strong> Dialogues contain main words and expression related to the topic of the lesson. In order you could understand the content of the dialogue there is a preliminary descriptions of the situation and the translation of all phrases of the dialogue. It is not necessary to learn the phrases from the dialogue. The work with the dialogue consists in repeating phrases after speaker and reading with/without the transcription.
</p>
<p>
<strong>Exercises with new words.</strong> These exercises contain the most important words related the topic of the lesson. As a rule, while doing tasks of the exercises, it is required to use the expressions studied in the previous lessons. Some tasks come with right answers, so if your answer does not agree with the right version you should find the mistake in your answer and repeat the correct variant.
</p>
<p>
<strong>Exercises with new expressions and constructions.</strong> These exercises contain various constructions which can be used to build phrases related to different topics. Besides, they may be accompanied by grammar comments.
</p>	
	
	
	
